  "journal": [
    {
      "id": "journal-session-12",
      "name": "Session 12 Notes",
      "content": "<h2>Session 12 — The Tomb Awaits</h2><p><strong>Date:</strong> Tarsakh 14</p><h3>Summary</h3><p>The party descended into the Tomb of the Nine Gods after spending two days mapping the exterior and neutralizing the guardian statues at the entrance.</p><h3>Key Events</h3><ul><li>Discovered the first puzzle chamber — the Scale of Moa</li><li>Kira successfully disarmed the poison dart trap (DC 22 thieves' tools)</li><li>Aldric's Detect Magic revealed three magical auras in the altar chamber</li><li>Omu Guardian combat — party spent significant resources</li></ul><h3>Treasure Found</h3><ul><li>Gold serpent idol (500 gp)</li><li>Scroll of Protection from Evil and Good</li><li>12 pp hidden in a secret compartment</li></ul><h3>Notes for Next Session</h3><p>Party is camping in the antechamber. They have 4 spell slots remaining between them. The north door requires a puzzle to open — foreshadow this.</p>",
      "ownership": {}
    },
    {
      "id": "journal-omu-lore",
      "name": "The City of Omu — Lore",
      "content": "<h2>Omu — The Forbidden City</h2><p>Once the greatest city in all of Chult, Omu was destroyed by the trickster gods after its people turned from worshipping them. The city now lies in a remote valley surrounded by cliffs, accessible only through treacherous jungle paths.</p><h3>The Nine Trickster Gods</h3><ul><li><strong>Eshowdow</strong> — God of shadows</li><li><strong>I'Jin</strong> — Goddess of whims</li><li><strong>Kubazan</strong> — God of boldness</li><li><strong>Moa</strong> — God of honesty</li><li><strong>Nangnang</strong> — Goddess of greed</li><li><strong>Obo'laka</strong> — Goddess of caution</li><li><strong>Papazotl</strong> — God of cunning</li><li><strong>Shagambi</strong> — Goddess of valor</li><li><strong>Wongo</strong> — God of disharmony</li></ul><h3>The Death Curse</h3><p>The Soulmonger, a powerful necromantic artifact, is draining the life force of everyone who has ever been resurrected. It must be destroyed.</p>",
      "ownership": {}
    }
  ],

